                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d860">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.113 (Manchuria) Petroleum/82: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-15T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Your 31, February 15, 11 a.m. The Department perceives no objection to joint
                    informal oral representations and approves the suggestion contained in the
                    penultimate sentence of your telegram.<note n="78" xml:id="d860fn78">The
                        Ambassador in Japan reported in telegram No. 34, February 19, 6 p.m., that
                        joint oral representations were made that day and were received favorably
                        (693.113 (Manchuria) Petroleum/83).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
